Load Training Dataset

In [4]:
# Load Training

path = ('Dataset/dataset/train')
training_data = [os.path.join(dp, f) for dp, dn, filenames in os.walk(path) for f in filenames if os.path.splitext(f)[1] == '.png']
In [5]:
training_images = []
training_labels = []
for i in tqdm(training_data):
  cv_img = cv2.imread(i)
  cv_img = cv2.resize(cv_img, (69, 69), interpolation = cv2.INTER_NEAREST)
  training_images.append(cv_img)

  if("Barred Spiral" in i):
    training_labels.append("Barred Spiral")
  elif("Cigar Shaped Smooth" in i):
    training_labels.append("Cigar Shaped Smooth")
  elif("Disturbed" in i):
    training_labels.append("Disturbed")
  elif("Edge-on with Bulge" in i):
    training_labels.append("Edge-on with Bulge")
  elif("Edge-on without Bulge" in i):
    training_labels.append("Edge-on without Bulge")
  elif("In-between Round Smooth" in i):
    training_labels.append("In-between Round Smooth")
  elif("Merging" in i):
    training_labels.append("Merging")
  elif("Round Smooth" in i):
    training_labels.append("Round Smooth")
  elif("Unbarred Loose Spiral" in i):
    training_labels.append("Unbarred Loose Spiral")
  else:
    training_labels.append("Unbarred Tight Spiral")

encoder = preprocessing.LabelEncoder()

Step 5: Build Machine Learning Model¶

Machine Learning Model

In [11]:
# Define Model

model = Sequential()

model.add(Flatten(input_shape=(69, 69, 3)))
model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(10, activation='softmax'))

model_optimizer = Adam(learning_rate =0.001)

Complile Model

In [12]:
# Compile Model

training_images = np.array(training_images) / 255
testing_images = np.array(testing_images) / 255
training_labels_encoded = np.array(training_labels_encoded)

model.compile(optimizer=model_optimizer, loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=["accuracy"])
reduceLR = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='accuracy', factor=.001, patience=1, min_delta=0.01, mode="auto")
History = model.fit(training_images, training_labels_encoded, epochs = 25, callbacks=[reduceLR])

Step 6: Predictions on Training Data¶

In [14]:
# Predictions
y_pred = model.predict(training_images).argmax(axis=1)

# Accuracy Score
accuracy = accuracy_score(training_labels_encoded, y_pred)
print("\n\n======================")
print("Accuracy Score:")
print("======================\n\n")
print("  Accuracy: ", round(accuracy*100,2), "%")

# Classification Report
report = classification_report(training_labels_encoded, y_pred)
print("\n\n======================")
print("Classification Report:")
print("======================\n\n")
print(report)

# Confusion Matrix
matrix = confusion_matrix(training_labels_encoded, y_pred)
print("\n\n=================")
print("Confusion Matrix:")
print("=================\n\n")
print(matrix)

# Heat Map
print("\n\n===============================")
print("Confusion Matrix with Heat MAP:")
print("===============================\n\n")
confusion_matrix_heatmap = confusion_matrix(training_labels_encoded, y_pred, normalize = 'true')
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(10,7)})
sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix_heatmap, annot=True)
